ohler|first=Chris|url=https://www.wired.com/2012/12/bound-high-virtual-boy/|title=When Games get Canceled, These Guys Bring them Back to Life|publisher=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]|date=December 12, 2012|access-date=2019-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222192532/https://www.wired.com/2012/12/bound-high-virtual-boy/|archive-date=December 22, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=thunderstruck|url=https://www.planetvb.com/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?post_id=41980#forumpost41980|title=Bound High official ROM difference|website=planetvb.com|date=December 24, 2018|access-date=2019-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190202234854/https://www.planetvb.com/modules/newbb/viewtopic.php?post_id=41980|archive-date=2 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"| '''''[[Donkey Kong Country 2: Diddy's Kong Quest]]'''''\n| Platform\n| [[Rare (company)|Rare]]\n| {{N/A}}\n| {{date|2017-12-16}}\n| Former Rare artist Steven Hurst stated that he and a [[Video game programmer|programmer]] used [[Sprite (computer graphics)|sprite]]s from ''[[Donkey Kong Land]]''.<ref name=\"RareGamerVBDKC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.raregamer.co.uk/games/donkey-kong-virtual-boy-scribes-excerpts/|title=Donkey Kong Virtual Boy Scribes Excerpts|website=raregamer.co.uk|date=2017|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=http://archive.today/oABc7|archive-date=2020-04-06|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"DFRetroDKC\">{{cite web|last=Linneman|first=John|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/digitalfoundry-2017-retro-donkey-kong-country-killer-instinct|title=DF Retro takes on Donkey Kong Country and Killer Instinct \u2022 The story of Rare's SGI revolution - as told by the developers|work=[[Eurogamer]]|publisher=Gamer Network Ltd.|date=December 16, 2017|access-date=2019-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320001528/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/digitalfoundry-2017-retro-donkey-kong-country-killer-instinct|archive-date